# Trivy suppressions for spring-on-k8s
#
# This is a learning/demo project for Spring Boot on Kubernetes. Production-grade
# Pod Security hardening (securityContext, read-only rootfs, seccomp, non-default
# namespace, pinned image digests, resource requests, capability drop) is
# intentionally out of scope — the demo focuses on Spring Boot + K8s probes +
# ConfigMap mount + Carvel (ytt/kapp) deployment mechanics.
#
# The findings below are valid production concerns; they are suppressed only for
# this specific demo. Do NOT copy these suppressions into production manifests.

# Pod Security — securityContext / capabilities / seccomp
KSV001    # allowPrivilegeEscalation should be false
KSV003    # capabilities.drop should include ALL
KSV004    # capabilities.drop should be set
KSV012    # runAsNonRoot should be true
KSV014    # readOnlyRootFilesystem should be true (Spring Boot needs /tmp writeable)
KSV020    # runAsUser > 10000
KSV021    # runAsGroup > 10000
KSV030    # seccompProfile.type should be RuntimeDefault
KSV104    # container should specify seccomp profile
KSV106    # container should drop ALL capabilities
KSV118    # container using default security context

# Resource management — demo uses memory limit only
KSV011    # resources.limits.cpu
KSV015    # resources.requests.cpu
KSV016    # resources.requests.memory

# Image / registry — demo uses Docker Hub :latest
KSV013    # should specify image tag (not :latest)
KSV125    # image from untrusted registry (3-digit form)
KSV0125   # image from untrusted registry (4-digit form — newer trivy versions)
AVD-KSV-0125  # image from untrusted registry (AVD-prefixed form)

# Namespace — demo uses default namespace (kapp deploys into --into-ns at apply-time)
KSV110    # should set metadata.namespace to non-default

# Dockerfile — HEALTHCHECK is redundant; K8s liveness/readiness probes on
# /actuator/health/liveness + /actuator/health/readiness are the authoritative
# health source for this service (see k8s/deployment.yml).
DS-0026
DS0026

# Dependency CVE suppressions: NONE.
#
# Spring Boot 4.1.0 GA (pom.xml parent) manages tomcat-embed-* 11.0.22 and
# Jackson 3.1.4 — past the fixes for the previously-suppressed upstream CVEs
# (Tomcat CVE-2026-34483/-34486/-34487/-34500, fixed 11.0.21; Jackson
# GHSA-2m67-wjpj-xhg9, fixed 3.1.1). Those suppressions were removed when the
# GA bump landed (verified: `trivy fs --severity HIGH,CRITICAL` reports zero
# findings with no ignorefile). Renovate tracks spring-boot-starter-parent; add
# a dependency suppression here only for a newly-disclosed CVE awaiting an
# upstream-fixed release, with a dated rationale.

# Base image OS package suppressions: NONE.
#
# The runtime base is eclipse-temurin:25-jre-alpine (Alpine 3.23, digest-pinned
# in Dockerfile, tracked by Renovate). The runtime stage runs
# `RUN apk --no-cache upgrade` so baked-in OS packages are pulled up to the
# latest in the pinned Alpine 3.23 branch at build time — newly-disclosed CVEs
# that Alpine has already fixed clear immediately instead of waiting on the
# Adoptium base rebuild (see docs/adr/0001-runtime-base-image.md Addendum
# 2026-06; the trigger was CVE-2026-45447 in openssl 3.5.6-r0 → 3.5.7-r0).
# Prefer this real fix (and Renovate-driven base bumps) over suppression; add
# OS-package suppressions here only for a genuinely-unfixable finding where
# Alpine has NOT yet shipped a fixed package, with a dated rationale.
#
# History: the prior Google distroless base (gcr.io/distroless/java21-debian13)
# required five standing OS-package suppressions for upstream-fixed CVEs that
# the published distroless rebuild lagged on. Those were dropped when we
# migrated off distroless — see docs/adr/0001-runtime-base-image.md.
